==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repartee
<hw>Rep`ar*tee"</hw> <pr>(r?p`3r-t?")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>repartie</ets>, fr. <ets>repartir</ets> to reply, depart again;
pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- <ets>partir</ets> to part, depart. See
<er>Part</er>.]</ety> <def>A smart, ready, and witty reply.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cupid was as bad as he;⟦br⟧
Hear but the youngster's <qex>repartee</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Retort; reply. See <er>Retort</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repartee</ent>⟦br⟧

